y on this region, but with a less steep\nbehaviour. We note that numerous metre-sized boulders, which exhibit a smaller\nopposition effect, also appear spectrally redder than their surroundings. In\nthis region, we found no evidence linking observed bright spots to exposed\nwater-ice-rich material. We fitted our dataset using the Hapke 2008 photometric\nmodel. The region overflown is globally as dark as the whole nucleus (geometric\nalbedo of 6.8{\\%}) and it has a high porosity value in the uppermost-layers\n(86{\\%}). These results of the photometric analysis at a decimetre scale\nindicate that the photometric properties of the flown-by region are similar to\nthose previously found for the whole nucleus.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 31 Oct 2016 20:00:06 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-02"}
